data.title: The Sheffield Daily Telegraph [Sir William Christopher Leng] by Spy: (1890) Art / Print / Poster
data.meta_description: 1890 - Condition: Good - VANITY FAIR SPY CARTOON WC Leng 'The Sheffield Daily Telegraph' Newspapers 1890. Antique chromolithograph (colour) Vanity Fair "Spy" cartoon/caricature print; Spy (08 March 1890. This date is printed above the image). Picture size 19 x 33cm (7.5 x 13 inches); Overall page size approximately 25 x 37cm (10 x 15 inches). Condition: Good. A copy of the original biographical notes published with the print will be provided. There is nothing printed on the reverse side, which is plain. LENG Sir William Christopher. By Spy. Born Hull 1825. Brought up in the chemists' trade. Wrote for Dundee Advertiser in 1859. Rose to become Editor and Proprietor of the Sheffield Daily Telegraph. Smoking cigar. (Newspapers) Picture size 19 x 33cm (7.5 x 13 inches); Overall page size approximately 25 x 37cm (10 x 15 inches) - The Sheffield Daily Telegraph [Sir William Christopher Leng]
